SVGForeignObjectElement.summary: The SVGForeignObjectElement interface provides access to the properties of foreignObject elements, as well as methods to manipulate them.

SVGForeignObjectElementHeight.summary: The height read-only property of the interface describes the height of the <foreignObject> element. It reflects the computed value of the {{SVGAttr("height")}} attribute on the foreignObject element.

remarks.para: The attribute value is a <length>, <percentage>, or <number>. The numeric value of the is the y-coordinate of the <foreignObject> element in the user coordinate system.

SVGForeignObjectElementWidth.summary: The width read-only property of the interface describes the width of the <foreignObject> element. It reflects the computed value of the {{SVGAttr("width")}} attribute on the foreignObject element.

remarks.para: The attribute value is a <length>, <percentage>, or <number>. The numeric value of the is the y-coordinate of the <foreignObject> element in the user coordinate system.

SVGForeignObjectElementX.summary: The x read-only property of the interface describes the x-axis coordinate of the <foreignObject> element. It reflects the computed value of the {{SVGAttr("x")}} attribute on the foreignObject element.

remarks.para: The attribute value is a <length>, <percentage>, or <number>. The numeric value of the is the x-coordinate of the <foreignObject> element in the user coordinate system.

remarks.para: The attribute value is a <length>, <percentage>, or <number>. The numeric value of the is the y-coordinate of the <foreignObject> element in the user coordinate system.
